===Alternative forms===
* In all regions except Japan, the middle component is written {{l|mul|犬}}, which is the orthodox form found in the {{w|Kangxi dictionary}}.
* In Japanese {{w|shinjitai}}, the middle component is written {{l|mul|大}} instead of {{l|mul|犬}} (the upper right dot is missing). Due to {{w|Han unification}}, both forms are encoded using the same [[code point]]. This character may appear to be different depending on the font used.
* A {{w|CJK Compatibility Ideographs|CJK compatibility ideograph}} exists at <code>U+FA38</code> for the {{w|kyūjitai}} form of {{lang|ja|器}} which has {{l|mul|犬}} as the middle component.
* Another character, {{l|mul|𠾖}} (<code>U+20F96</code>) exists for the historical form found in the {{w|Ming dynasty}} {{lang|zh|《直音篇》}} Chinese dictionary<!-- Refer http://dict.variants.moe.edu.tw/bookpiece/062/43430.png --> which is similar to Japanese {{w|shinjitai}}.

