===Etymology 1===
{{ja-kanjitab|き|y=o|alt=噐}}

From {{bor|ja|ltc|-|sort=き}} {{m|zh|器|tr=khij<sup>H</sup>||vessel; instrument}}.

====Pronunciation====
{{ja-pron|き}}
* When used as a suffix, the resulting term has a [[downstep]] either right before, or one [[mora]] before, the ''ki''.
:* If the preceding syllable has only one mora (as in ''ga'' or ''tsu''), the downstep occurs just after that mora:
::: {{m|ja|瓦器||unglazed earthenware}}: {{lang|ja|{{ja-accent/down|が}}き}} <span class="Latn">{{monospace|[gáꜜkì]}}</span>
::: {{m|ja|空気予熱器|tr=kūki yonetsuki||air pre-heater}}: {{lang|ja|く{{ja-accent/high|うきよね}}{{ja-accent/down|つ}}き}} <span class="Latn">{{monospace|[kùúkí yónétsúꜜkì]}}</span>
:* If the preceding syllable has two [[morae]] (as in ''zen'' or ''tei''), the downstep occurs between the two morae:
::: {{l|ja|安全器|tr=anzenki||safety cut-out}}: {{lang|ja|あ{{ja-accent/high|ん}}{{ja-accent/down|ぜ}}んき}} <span class="Latn">{{monospace|[àńzéꜜǹkì]}}</span>
::: {{l|ja|円弧測定器|tr=enko sokuteiki||cyclometer}}: {{lang|ja|え{{ja-accent/high|んこそく}}{{ja-accent/down|て}}いき}} <span class="Latn">{{monospace|[èńkó sókútéꜜèkì]}}</span>

